OL,3,CNHS to open more 'mental health A&Es'
OL,4,Cto relieve pressure on hospitals
OL,6,FSir Jim Mackey, the chief executive of
OL,7,FNHS England, told the paper: "Crowded
OL,8,FA&Es are not designed to treat people
OL,9,Fin mental health crisis.
OL,11,F"We need to do better, which is why we
OL,12,Fare pioneering a new model of care
OL,13,Fwhere patients get the right support
OL,14,Fin the right setting.
OL,16,F"As well as relieving pressure on our
OL,17,Fbusy A&Es, mental health crisis
OL,18,Fassessment centres can speed up access
OL,19,Fto appropriate care, offering people
OL,20,Fthe help they need much sooner so they
OL,21,Fcan stay out of hospital."
